# Item Duplication

**Item Duplication** is a fundamental glitch in Dark Souls that allows players to bypass standard game mechanics to multiply items in their inventory. While some of these items can be found or farmed normally, this technique enables you to instantly obtain a much higher quantity than would be possible through regular gameplay.\

By using this glitch, you can rapidly accumulate essential resources such as **Souls**, **Humanity**, and **Upgrade Materials** (like Titanite Shards or Twinkling Titanite). This provides a massive advantage early in the run, allowing for high-level weapon reinforcements and rapid character leveling without the need for traditional farming.

Video by Catalystz explaining in-depht how item duping works: [https://youtu.be/4lZiJqSwjk0](https://youtu.be/4lZiJqSwjk0)

## Confirmation Box dupe

**The Confirmation Box Dupe** is a menu-layering glitch that allows players to consume a single item (such as a Soul or Humanity) as if they were using a massive stack. By default, the game initializes this value at 99, but it can be manipulated further.

By opening the 'Drop' prompt on a stack of 999 arrows for example and then canceling the action to don't loose them, the player "stores" that specific quantity in the game's memory. Through precise menu navigation, this stored value is then applied to a consumable. This trick grants the benefit of 999 uses instantly, bypassing the need to actually possess that many items.

