## \

Negative Dupe

\
**Negative Duping** is a **form** of menu-layering that exploits the logic behind item quantity calculations. By storing a negative quantity in the **game's memory**, you can trick it **into granting** a positive amount of items. This glitch is very **useful** because **it allows the player to** duplicate items without **a** confirmation box like upgrade materials, boss souls, or **covenant** items. I**t is used** in almost all of the glitched runs of the game.

The most common way to do it is for PC only since it require the use of a mouse.

